{"id":"TGR-s50.6","title":"xCPS: Implement Noether charge Q","description":"Implement the Noether charge (d-2)-form Q^{μν}[ξ] such that on-shell J^μ = ∇_ν Q^{μν}. For EH gravity:
  Q^{μν} = -∇^{[μ} ξ^{ν]}

The Noether charge is the integrand of conserved charges: H[ξ] = ∫_∂Σ Q. For Killing vectors, this gives Komar integrals. For horizons, this gives black hole entropy.

Requires potential extraction (finding Q from dQ = J). Add to src/phase_space/.

Ground truth: Wald (1990) Eq 2.8; Iyer & Wald, PRD 50, 846 (1994).

Acceptance: noether_charge(J, or equivalently L, field, xi) returns Q^{μν}. Verify for EH: Q = -∇^[μ ξ^ν].","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"tobias.osborne@itp.uni-hannover.de","created_at":"2026-03-14T22:15:17Z","created_by":"tobiasosborne","updated_at":"2026-03-14T22:15:17Z"}
